1. In `_flush()` when `_inFlightWrites <= 0 && !_waitForDrain`
2. In the write stream's drain handler when `!this._queue.size` (original) or `this._queue.size` (mutated)

So the mutation would cause the dirty `drain` event to fire when there are still items in the queue. My test approach is correct.

